response.original_title: Del Harrison: From the Mouth of A Black Woman
response.overview: Del Harrison realized a few things: that white people in LA are cool, her "Nigerian" heritage is in question and her recent divorce from an interracial church was the right thing to do and a "certain type of work" is legal in particular situations. Del's impeccable storytelling transcends from her jokes to her original music as she is accompanied by a live band and her talented singing sisters to deliver a night of magic while we peak inside her life off the stage in short docustyle videos.
response.title: Del Harrison: From the Mouth of A Black Woman
